items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 1/The Wire Season 1 Episode 01 - The Target.avi
items.summary:
'... when it's not your turn.' - McNulty.

Baltimore homicide detective Jimmy McNulty gets into hot water and winds up assigned to a detail of narcotics outcasts charged with investigating drug lord Avon Barksdale and his powerful operation in Franklin Terrace. Meanwhile, Avon's nephew D'Angelo is fresh off beating a murder rap, but he finds himself demoted upon his return to the gang.
items.title: The Target

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 1/The Wire Season 1 Episode 02 - The Detail.avi
items.summary:
'You cannot lose if you do not play.' - Marla Daniels.

McNulty feels the heat when a witness who testified against D'Angelo is found murdered. Meanwhile, Greggs is given the lay of the land regarding Avon Barksdale's key players, and Herc, Carver and Prez find big-time trouble at the towers.
items.title: The Detail

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 1/The Wire Season 1 Episode 03 - The Buys.avi
items.summary:
"The king stay the king." - D'Angelo.  

The early-morning 'field interviews' by Herc, Carver and Prez result in a minor riot, a boy losing an eye and some bad publicity for the department. On the other side of the law, D'Angelo teaches Wallace and Bodie how to play the game (chess) and later impresses Bell with his 'take' from the low-rises.
items.title: The Buys

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 1/The Wire Season 1 Episode 04 - Old Cases.avi
items.summary:
"It's a thin line 'tween heaven and here." - Bubbles.  

Greggs and McNulty try to get Hardcase to turn informant as arraignment begins for those caught in the raid. Barksdale places a bounty on the head of rival gang leader Omar. Meanwhile, McNulty takes Bubbles on a cultural field trip, and Herc and Carver try to track down Bodie.
items.title: Old Cases

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 1/The Wire Season 1 Episode 05 - The Pager.avi
items.summary:
"..a little slow, a little late." - Avon Barksdale.  

McNulty's detail finally gets 'clone' pagers to track Barksdale and his gang, but nobody can crack the codes used by the callers. Meanwhile, Bell instructs D'Angelo on how to school his lookouts while simultaneously flushing out a possible snitch. Later, Carver and Herc find Bodie, but their interrogation doesn't turn up results.
items.title: The Pager

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 1/The Wire Season 1 Episode 06 - The Wire.avi
items.summary:
"..and all the pieces matter." - Freamon. 

When Rawls looks to make a premature arrest for three murders that are linked to D'Angelo and Avon Barksdale, McNulty and Greggs must argue for a delay in order to preserve the valuable wiretap gains they have made. Meanwhile, Wallace and D'Angelo struggle with their consciences after Avon pays them blood money.
items.title: The Wire

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 1/The Wire Season 1 Episode 07 - One Arrest.avi
items.summary:
"A man must have a code." - Bunk.  

Tipped off by the wire, Greggs, Herc, Carver and Freamon make a bust, but the incident makes Avon and Stringer suspicious, leading them to close shop in the Pit. Meanwhile, Bunk and McNulty look for another witness in the Gant slaying and hunt a suspect known as 'Mr. Bird.'
items.title: One Arrest

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 1/The Wire Season 1 Episode 08 - Lessons.avi
items.summary:
"Come at the king, you best not miss." - Omar.  

An unlikely source gives McNulty the tag of a car driven by Stringer Bell. Meanwhile, Greggs and Carver bust a congressional aide carrying dirty cash, but are forced to let him go. Omar earns his 'loose cannon' moniker.
items.title: Lessons

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 1/The Wire Season 1 Episode 09 - Game Day.avi
items.summary:
"Maybe we won." - Herc.  

Barksdale plays an expensive game of one-upmanship with an east-side rival. Meanwhile, Herc and Carver take some cash off of Wee-Bey's hands, and Omar resurfaces with a bang.
items.title: Game Day

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 1/The Wire Season 1 Episode 10 - The Cost.avi
items.summary:
"And then he dropped the bracelets..." - Greggs.  

With Wallace in custody, McNulty and Daniels try to figure out what to do with him in the months before he testifies. Sydnor and Carver track down one of Barksdale's stash houses, and Prez shows off his 'gift for the paper trail.' McNulty's estranged wife Elena takes desperate measures after learning that he had their kids follow Stringer Bell.
items.title: The Cost

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 1/The Wire Season 1 Episode 11 - The Hunt.avi
items.summary:
"Dope on the damn table." - Daniels.  

The police turn up the heat on tracking down Savino, Wee-Bey and Little Man. Burrell orders Daniels to hit drug dealers for results that will impress the press. Barksdale sees his ranks thinning after the hit on Orlando. Bubbles tries to stay sober while scoping out the projects for McNulty; and Freamon determines there's a rat in the detail.
items.title: The Hunt

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 1/The Wire Season 1 Episode 12 - Cleaning Up.avi
items.summary:
"This is me, yo, right here." - Wallace.  

The low-rise pay phones are out of service, so McNulty and Daniels try to keep pace by tapping Barksdale's office. Bodie gets new responsibilities from Stringer; Freamon gives Shardene a 'new look'; and D'Angelo goes to NYC on an errand for his uncle. With the detail's future hanging in the balance, Daniels faces off against Burrell and his political allies.
items.title: Cleaning Up

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 1/The Wire Season 1 Episode 13 - Sentencing.avi
items.summary:
"all in the game..." - Traditional West Baltimore.  

Every crew has weak links--including Avon Barksdale's. With the heat turned up in the high-rises, Daniels and McNulty turn to a higher authority in an effort to crack the case wide open. Season finale.
items.title: Sentencing

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 2/The Wire Season 2 Episode 01 - Ebb Tide.avi
items.summary:
'Ain't never gonna be what it was.' -- Little Big Roy

Det. Jimmy McNulty--exiled to police-boat duty--makes a shocking discovery in the Baltimore harbor. Bodie drives to Philly to make a connection for the Barksdale crew and Stringer Bell takes the train to New York to feel out the crew's reticent suppliers.
items.title: Ebb Tide

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 2/The Wire Season 2 Episode 02 - Collateral Damage.avi
items.summary:
'They can chew you up, but they gotta spit you out.' -- McNulty

Major Valchek gets back at Sobotka for the church gift fiasco, and a feud begins. Valchek ups the ante by asking Deputy Commissioner Burrell for a detail to go after Sobotka. Avon Barksdale continues to run his empire from a prison cell--counseling his nephew D'Angelo and going after a guard who is harassing the organization's convicted hit-man Wee-Bey.
items.title: Collateral Damage

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 2/The Wire Season 2 Episode 03 - Hot Shots.avi
items.summary:
'What they need is a union.' -- Russell

Bunk and Freamon chase their crime scene, a container ship, to Philly. Lt. Cedric Daniels--disgusted with his exile to the evidence control unit--makes it known that he's leaving. On orders from Barksdale, Bell finds a way to set up the correctional officer who's been harassing Wee-Bey. McNulty pursues the identity of the Jane Doe found floating in the harbor.
items.title: Hot Shots

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 2/The Wire Season 2 Episode 04 - Hard Cases.avi
items.summary:
'If I hear the music, I'm gonna dance.' -- Greggs

Sobotka reprimands his nephew Nick for stealing the cameras and orders him to bring the cargo back--too late. McNulty is on a self-assigned moral mission to identify his floater, but his old partner, Bunk, says they have a more pressing matter at hand: to find Omar so he can testify against a Barksdale trigger man in one of last year's murders.
items.title: Hard Cases

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 2/The Wire Season 2 Episode 05 - Undertow.avi
items.summary:
'They used to make steel there, no?' -- Spiros Vondas

Ziggy loses his prized Camaro to drug dealers. Unable to dump the homicide investigation on other agencies, Rawls measures Bunk for the blame, if the cases go unsolved. Homicide detectives hand out grand jury summonses to stevedores involved in the homicide case, and port cop Beadie Russell talks to an old boyfriend to find out how cargo disappears from the docks.
items.title: Undertow

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 2/The Wire Season 2 Episode 06 - All Prologue.avi
items.summary:
'It don't matter that some fool say he different...' -- D'Angelo

Trying to let go of police work and return to his marriage, McNulty gives up on identifying his Jane Doe. In their investigation of Sobotka, the detectives discover a pattern in the computer and explain the connection to Daniels, but he still won't take the murders. Sobotka tries to play the political game on behalf of his union.
items.title: All Prologue

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 2/The Wire Season 2 Episode 07 - Backwash.avi
items.summary:
'Don't worry, kid. You're still on the clock.' -- Horseface

Russell tells Sobotka the investigation is over, but, in fact, a port computer is cloned, and when a container goes missing, the detectives follow. Simultaneously, Greggs and Prez tap into a circuit of Russian prostitutes. With two sets of evidence, the detail goes to Pearlman. Neither crime merits wiretap--but a drug connect could give the case legs.
items.title: Backwash

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 2/The Wire Season 2 Episode 08 - Duck and Cover.avi
items.summary:
'How come they don't fly away?' -- Ziggy

McNulty is back to his old self, on a drunken binge. Urged by fellow stevedores to fight Maui, Ziggy is again humiliated. Worried about McNulty, Bunk tries to get Daniels and Rawls to take him on. After some labor, the wiretap is up--just in time to catch another disappearing can. Sobotka meets with The Greek and Vondas, and they decide to change up.
items.title: Duck and Cover

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 2/The Wire Season 2 Episode 09 - Stray Rounds.avi
items.summary:
'The world is a smaller place now.' -- The Greek

Bodie's effort to improve sales ends disastrously, forcing Bell to rethink his strategy. Ziggy pulls Johnny Fifty into a new caper that should make the Greeks pay off big. McNulty, undercover and outnumbered in the brothel, awaits 'rescue.' Daniels and Pearlman stay cool as Valcheck fumes over the change of targets--and Burrell pulls the rug out from under him.
items.title: Stray Rounds

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 2/The Wire Season 2 Episode 10 - Storm Warnings.avi
items.summary:
'It pays to go with the union card every time.' -- Ziggy

The Detail uses satellite technology to its advantage. Bodie is unhappy that Proposition Joe's people are slinging on his turf, but business flows--until a new face arrives. Stringer Bell looks to an unlikely solution to the problem. Valcheck visits the FBI in an attempt to get real results on the docks. Ziggy's deal with Double-G goes bad in a big way.
items.title: Storm Warnings

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 2/The Wire Season 2 Episode 11 - Bad Dreams.avi
items.summary:
'I need to get clean' -- Sobotka

With the clock ticking, the Detail makes a desperate move, and Daniels reams out Landsman for dropping the ball. Nick's deceit is in the open as Sobotka is overwhelmed by bad news. The Greeks ease out of an encounter with the Detail, and Omar's suspicions are validated. The Detail hopes to find Vondas's boss, and Nick hopes to repair relations with the Greeks.
items.title: Bad Dreams

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 2/The Wire Season 2 Episode 12 - Port in a Storm.avi
items.summary:
'Business. Always business.' -- The Greek

The Detail has a setback, while Russell and Bunk revisit Philly to look for evidence. Brother Mouzone talks with Stringer Bell about their agreement, leaving Bell to contend with a dissatisfied Avon Barksdale. Bubbles and Johnny pull another caper and McNulty and Greggs return to the Westside, where they discover new connections.
items.title: Port in a Storm

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 3/The Wire Season 3 Episode 01 - Time After Time.avi
items.summary:
"Don't matter how many times you get burnt, you just keep doin' the same." -- Bodie

A wave of urban reform brings down the notorious Franklin Terrace public housing towers, forcing the Barksdale drug crew to find a new home. Stringer Bell uses a new sales strategy as he awaits Avon's return. McNulty and the Detail look to make a case against Stringer with a wiretap on a drug ring run by Proposition Joe.
items.title: Time After Time

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 3/The Wire Season 3 Episode 02 - All Due Respect.avi
items.summary:
"There's never been a paper bag." -- Colvin

Omar continues his bold strikes on Barksdale stash houses, now heavily guarded. Under orders from Stringer Bell, Bodie faces a critical test against Marlo, a fierce young dealer with lucrative corners. As the wire on Proposition Joe continues to yield little, McNulty launches his own reinvestigation of last year's prison suicide of D'Angelo Barksdale.
items.title: All Due Respect

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 3/The Wire Season 3 Episode 03 - Dead Soldiers.avi
items.summary:
"The gods will not save you." -- Burrell

Colvin feels the sting of Burrell and Rawls during a Comstat assessment of his district's felony numbers; a blown wiretap forces Daniels's detail to turn to a new target; Proposition Joe cautions Stringer Bell that the police have been tapping phones. Carcetti continues to curry favor in Mayor Royce's inner circle.
items.title: Dead Soldiers

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 3/The Wire Season 3 Episode 04 - Amsterdam.avi
items.summary: West Baltimore residents get surprising straight talk at a community meeting from Major Colvin. Bubbles finds gainful employment; Stringer lunches uptown; and Bunk dangles the promise of immunity to a group of corner boys, in exchange for help. Greggs learns how Marlo takes care of business as Bubbles instructs her on the next big thing: disposable cell phones.
items.title: Amsterdam

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 3/The Wire Season 3 Episode 05 - Straight and True.avi
items.summary:
"I had such fuckin' hopes for us." -- McNulty

Frustrated in his grass-roots reform efforts, Colvin arms himself with intelligence from Daniels's detail and personally delivers a message to the next level of corner management. McNulty sees Stringer Bell's legitimate business dealings as a sign that he is now unreachable as a drug target. Bubbles shakes the tree for Johnny one more time.
items.title: Straight and True

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 3/The Wire Season 3 Episode 06 - Homecoming.avi
items.summary:
"Just a gangster, I suppose." -- Avon Barksdale

Stringer Bell gets an education in construction management; Bunk uses shoe-leather to catch up with Omar and deliver a searing message; a frustrated Colvin unleashes the troops on the corner boys, ignoring his new edict; Avon sends Cutty and Slim Charles against Marlo; Bubbles refocuses the picture for Greggs.
items.title: Homecoming

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 3/The Wire Season 3 Episode 07 - Back Burners.avi
items.summary:
"Conscience do cost." -- Butchie

Herc discovers a blast from the past, which he belatedly reveals to his ex-colleagues. Daniels blows a gasket over the real reason the detail was reassigned from an investigation in Pimlico to the Western District. Stringer Bell learns from Donette that she's told Brianna about McNulty's visit and that Brianna is likely to talk to him.
items.title: Back Burners

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 3/The Wire Season 3 Episode 08 - Moral Midgetry.avi
items.summary:
"Crawl, walk, and then run." -- Clay Davis

With Amsterdam running full-tilt, Carver and Truck discover there really is no honor among thieves. Prez impresses the detail with what he's found out from Bodie's cell phone, information that sends McNulty and Greggs on a road trip. Colvin sees the benefits of his plan working but has overlooked the human toll, until the Deacon points out the deficiencies.
items.title: Moral Midgetry

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 3/The Wire Season 3 Episode 09 - Slapstick.avi
items.summary:
"...while you're waiting for moments that never come." -- Freamon

Responding to an officer's call for help, McNulty and Prez turn down the wrong alley, with unanticipated results. A Barksdale crew violates the unspoken Sunday truce with gunplay, increasing discontent among the New Day Co-op members. Stymied in his effort to open a gym, Cutty is surprised to find help from within Baltimore's power structure.
items.title: Slapstick

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 3/The Wire Season 3 Episode 10 - Reformation.avi
items.summary:
"Call it a crisis of leadership." -- Proposition Joe

Brother Mouzone returns to Baltimore on a mission of revenge and casts a wide net in his search for Omar, who has his own plan. Colvin manages, for now, to put off a 'Sun' reporter inquiring about Amsterdam. Carver learns how much he doesn't know about good policing, while Pearlman and Daniels plead their case for a new kind of wiretap to Judge Phelan.
items.title: Reformation

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 3/The Wire Season 3 Episode 11 - Middle Ground.avi
items.summary:
"We don't need to dream no more." -- Stringer Bell

The wire begins to yield information about the Barksdale organization, though finding links to the top proves elusive. Stringer and Avon reflect on how far they've come, with each harboring plans for the future. Tipped by Burrell, Carcetti sees Amsterdam for himself and weighs the benefits against the political reality.
items.title: Middle Ground

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 3/The Wire Season 3 Episode 12 - Mission Accomplished.avi
items.summary:
"...we fight on the lie." -- Slim Charles

In the Season Three finale, a reticent Avon readies his troops for a war against Marlo. Meanwhile, as the detail works towards the top rungs of the Barksdale organization, McNulty reassesses his pursuit of Stringer Bell and the path he's chosen for himself. While Royce continues to grapple with Amsterdam, Burrell offers a deal to minimize the fallout.
items.title: Mission Accomplished

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 4/The Wire Season 4 Episode 01 - Boys of Summer.avi
items.summary:
"Lambs to the slaughter here." - Marcia Donnelly

Four West Baltimore boys wrestle with what to do with the rest of their summer vacation as the new fall school year approaches. Bodie deals with his corner running slower than usual so he decides to take on a runner. Marlo believes he has finally solved the problem that Stringer could never figure out. Freamon, Greggs, and Sydnor go to Pearlman to see if she will issue City Hall subpoenas. Meanwhile, the mayoral race heats up as  Mayor Royce and his primary challenger, Tommy Carcetti each hit campaign trail. Prez begins preparing for his new career in higher education, while McNulty ends up turning down a promotion.
items.title: Boys of Summer

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 4/The Wire Season 4 Episode 02 - Soft Eyes.avi
items.summary:
"I still wake up white in a city that ain't." - Carcetti

In the hopes of possibly saving her job, Pearlman and Freamon continue arguing over the subpoenas, as the election draws closer.  Carcetti drops a bombshell on Royce during their televised debate, while Herc makes a shocking discovery about the Mayor himself. Marlo decides to help the young kids in their preparation for school. Namond gets some advice from his father, Wee-Bey. Bubbles decides to bring in an apprentice to help out his business, while Cutty continues his two jobs; landscaping and boxing mentor.
items.title: Soft Eyes

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 4/The Wire Season 4 Episode 03 - Home Rooms.avi
items.summary:
"I love the first day, man. Everybody all friendly an' shit." - Namond Brice

Prez is shocked by his students; Royce strikes back against Carcetti; Rawls begins to gut the major case unit from the inside; Colvin embarks on a new career.
items.title: Home Rooms

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 4/The Wire Season 4 Episode 04 - Refugees.avi
items.summary:
"No one wins. One side just loses more slowly." - Prez

Freamon and Greggs move to Homicide, while Herc and Dozerman join Marimow in the lackluster Major Crimes Unit. Cutty gets a "custodial" job at Tilghman School picking up truants, but struggles to make progress while trying to mentor Michael. Bubbles works to get Sherrod back in school as an 8th grader. Burrell finds a way to sabotage the state-witness murder investigation before the election,  impacting Greggs. Prez's struggles as a teacher continue while Bodie finds himself working for a new "company". Meanwhile, Colvin pitches his pilot program to the middle school and Carcetti meets with a constituency when he knows that they won't support him regardless of what he says.  Randy is faced with a dilemma after being busted for his candy scam and Proposition Joe plays Marlo in a high-stakes heist.
items.title: Refugees

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 4/The Wire Season 4 Episode 05 - Alliances.avi
items.summary:
"If you with us, you with us." - Chris Partlow

Commissioner Burrell loses Royce's support; Chris Partlow tries to recruit Michael to become a soldier in Marlo's unit; Dukie shows Randy and the boys that the missing are really dead; Odell Watkins drops his support for Royce and considers an offer from Councilman Carcetti.
items.title: Alliances

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 4/The Wire Season 4 Episode 06 - Margin of Error.avi
items.summary: Carcetti responds to a campaign smear.  Randy is accused of a serious transgression. Colvin's special class gets its first enlistees.
items.title: Margin of Error

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 4/The Wire Season 4 Episode 07 - Unto Others.avi
items.summary:
"Aw yeah. That golden rule." - The Bunk

Omar calls in a favor to the police; Carcetti gets advice from the ex-mayor and then Mayor Royce and his team; Cutty finds out why Spider has been avoiding him and explains to the rest of his boxers that it won't happen again; Prez makes a break through with his students; Herc loses his camera; Greggs solves the Braddock case with soft eyes; Bubbles gets robbed repeatedly and searches for Sherrod; Namond begins to work a package and finds it hard to get suspended from school; Daniels catches Carcetti's eye.
items.title: Unto Others

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 4/The Wire Season 4 Episode 08 - Corner Boys.avi
items.summary:
"We got our thing, but it's just part of the big thing." - Zenobia

Prez wants to teach off curriculum. Carcetti visits the Homicide Department and goes on ride-a-longs for drug busts. Colvin and Dr. Parneti's class discuss the Corner Boy rules. Bunk convinces Holley to take another look at the Old Face Andre/Omar Little case. Herc and Dozerman begin shaking down Marlo and his crew as they try to have their surveillance camera returned. Chris Partlow and Snoop look to send the New York crew a message. Marlo asks Proposition Joe to look into Herc. Michael's father comes home, while Namond recruits a lieutenant.
items.title: Corner Boys

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 4/The Wire Season 4 Episode 09 - Know Your Place.avi
items.summary:
"Might as well dump 'em, get another." - Proposition Joe

Herc and Dozerman search for Little Kevin; Omar gets out of jail; Carcetti has his first meeting with the City Council; Prez and the teachers begin teaching the test; Proposition Joe lets Marlo know Major Crimes is after him; Bubbles looks to Kima and Herc to help him out; Bubbles delivers Little Kevin to Herc; Old Face Andre goes into hiding but Proposition Joe sells him out; Bug's father gets in Michael's face; Michael takes his problems to Marlo; Daniels and Valchek gets promoted; Omar and Renaldo monitor Marlo's activities.
items.title: Know Your Place

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 4/The Wire Season 4 Episode 10 - Misgivings.avi
items.summary:
"World goin' one way, people another." -Poot

Walker catches Donut boosting cars and teaches him a lesson; Commissioner Burrell gets advice from Senator Davis; Little Kevin has a talk with Marlo and regrets it; Herc ignores Bubbles call and regrets it; the Area Superintendent questions the success of Colvin and Parenti's project class; Senator Davis attempts to con Carcetti; Carver arrests Namond but keeps him out of baby booking; Burrell has the police force juke the numbers with street sweeps; Marlo puts the word out that Randy is a snitch; Elena sees McNulty as a grown up; Chris Partlow and Snoop target Bug's father for Michael.
items.title: Misgivings

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 4/The Wire Season 4 Episode 11 - A New Day.avi
items.summary:
"You play in dirt, you get dirty." - McNulty

Randy has trouble with his friends at school, while Carcetti faces a huge dilemma. Meanwhile, Omar visits Proposition Joe, while Freamon reveals a secret.
items.title: A New Day

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 4/The Wire Season 4 Episode 12 - That's Got His Own.avi
items.summary:
"That all there is to it?" - Bubbles

While searching for the missing bodies, Freamon goes around the chain of command after being rebuked by Landsman. Carcetti finds that his promises of raises could be undermined by the school debt, forcing him to consider groveling before the Governor for money to pay it off. Colvin tries to keep his experimental class funded. Bubbles considers taking extreme measures to get rid of the man who continues to steal from him. Prez is concerned about Dukie's academic promotion. Omar orchestrates another big sting while Namond and Cutty get a first-hand taste of the "new" Michael. Carver's promise to look out for Randy ends up looking empty.
items.title: That's Got His Own

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 4/The Wire Season 4 Episode 13 - Final Grades.avi
items.summary:
"If animal trapped call 410-844-6286" - Baltimore, traditional

Burrell tries to help Daniels. Bubbles' big plan backfires and leaves him in big trouble. Colvin tries to find a solution for Namond while Omar makes new plans. McNulty tries to pay back his debt.
items.title: Final Grades

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 5/The Wire Season 5 Episode 01 - More With Less.avi
items.summary:
"The bigger the lie, the more they believe." - Bunk Moreland.

McNulty and the detail continue to stake out Marlo and his crew.  Recently promoted Sergeant Carver is met with complaints concerning unpaid overtime.  Meanwhile, Haynes deals with cutbacks, but is still able to expose a politician's connection to a drug dealer; and Joe, Marlo, Fatface Rick meet to divide up the drug trade across Baltimore.
items.title: More with Less

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 5/The Wire Season 5 Episode 02 - Unconfirmed Reports.avi
items.summary:
"This ain't Aruba, bitch." - Bunk Moreland

Freamon keeps a look out for Marlo, who is putting together a deal with Avon Barksdale.  Davis goes to Burrell for help, but finds that the commissioner's hands are tied.  Whiting puts together a series on broad strokes.
items.title: Unconfirmed Reports

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 5/The Wire Season 5 Episode 03 - Not For Attribution.avi
items.summary:
"They're dead where it doesn't count." - Fletcher

Mayor Carcetti's police department plan is leaked.  Marlo turns to Proposition Joe for help.  Meanwhile, McNulty strikes up an unexpected ally -- Freamon.
items.title: Not for Attribution

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 5/The Wire Season 5 Episode 04 - Transitions.avi
items.summary:
"Buyer's market out there." - Templeton

Omar plots his revenge for his former associates murder now that he's returned from exile. Gus stresses the need for a city-court reporter, after missing out on a grand jury probe. Carcetti finds there are strings attached in his desire to get rid of Burrell. While McNulty investigates the deaths of homeless men, Freamon needs the help of an old friend. Also, Marlo looks to the future in his dealings with the Greeks.
items.title: Transitions

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 5/The Wire Season 5 Episode 05 - React Quotes.avi
items.summary:
"Just because they're in the street doesn't mean they lack opinions." - Haynes

While the crew awaits a showdown with Omar, Marlo celebrates a business deal. Meanwhile, at the Sun, McNulty and Freamon take advantage of a development regarding the murder of the homeless people, while Dukie heads to Cutty's gym. Also, Herc does Carver a favor as a means to make amends for his past behavior, while Davis takes his case to the court of public opinion.
items.title: React Quotes

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 5/The Wire Season 5 Episode 06 - The Dickensian Aspect.avi
items.summary:
"If you have a problem with this. I understand completely." - Freamon

Marlo's crew goes on full alert after Omar's mysterious disappearance. Meanwhile, Carcetti concentrates on the plight of the homeless, while Bunk has an interview with a witness connected with the row-house case, and Templeton looks to a follow up to his recent front page story.
items.title: The Dickensian Aspect

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 5/The Wire Season 5 Episode 07 - Took.avi
items.summary:
"They don't teach it in law school." - Pearlman

After cooking up another scheme for the homeless case, McNulty and Lester become popular figures. Davis is set for his day in court by collecting the best legal assistance money can buy. Plus, Michael has brushes with the wrong side of the law, while Gus seeks help for an old story by going outside the Sun.
items.title: Took

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 5/The Wire Season 5 Episode 08 - Clarifications.avi
items.summary:
"A lie ain't a side of a story. It's just a lie." - Terry Hanning

A shift in the police department sends Carver to a new location. Meanwhile, Carcetti is forced to put his political future in jeopardy, Haynes digs deeper into Templeton's work, and an important case has a breakthrough by Sydnor, while Fletcher continues working with Bubbles.
items.title: Clarifications

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 5/The Wire Season 5 Episode 09 - Late Editions.avi
items.summary:
"Deserve got nuthin' to do with it." - Snoop

A promising lead makes Freamon's hard work worthwhile, although McNulty doesn't feel like a celebration. Michael is suspicious about his latest assignment;.Haynes gets fresh eyes to help with fact-checking. Namond's debating skills make Colvin proud. Davis points a finger at Levy and the courts. And Bubbles recounts a recent temptation overcome.
items.title: Late Editions

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Wire/Season 5/The Wire Season 5 Episode 10 - 30.avi
items.summary:
"...the life of kings." - H.L. Mencken

A damaging report by Pearlman and Daniels gets a reaction from Carcetti, while Haynes finds little support for his concerns about a reporters work from the bosses. Meanwhile, McNulty wants to put a homeless case to an end, Dukie searches for an old mentor and a fallen officer is given a wake.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Survivorman/Survivorman.S01.720p.HDTV.AC3.x264-NTb/Survivorman.S01E01.720p.HDTV.AC3.x264-NTb.mkv
items.summary: The Boreal forest of Northern Canada is a vast tract of wilderness stretching from the Atlantic Ocean to the Pacific. It is home to moose and beaver, crisscrossed by rivers and lakes and frost-free for only about three months of the year. Les intentionally tips his canoe in mid-stream and crawls from the icy waters onto shore where he does a quick inventory of his supplies. A handful of cashews and beef jerky, a solitary match, a multi-tool and 50 lbs of camera equipment to document the next seven days in the bush.
items.title: Canadian Boreal Forest

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Survivorman/Survivorman.S01.720p.HDTV.AC3.x264-NTb/Survivorman.S01E02.720p.HDTV.AC3.x264-NTb.mkv
items.summary: The Sonora Desert in the South-Western United States covers an area of approximately 120,000 square miles. It is an arid, seemingly barren environment with scorching daytime highs and freezing overnight lows. Riding a dirt bike out into the official middle of nowhere, Les simulates a break-down scenario. He empties out the contents of his pack - half a gallon of water, a snack bar and his multi-tool-7 more days!
items.title: Arizona Desert

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Survivorman/Survivorman.S01.720p.HDTV.AC3.x264-NTb/Survivorman.S01E03.720p.HDTV.AC3.x264-NTb.mkv
items.summary: A Costa Rican getaway - as far removed from everyday living as you can imagine: lush rainforests and deserted tropical beaches. Marooned on Costa Rica's Osa Peninsula, Les "Survivorman" Stroud has only a few items to aid him for the next 7 days: swimming goggles, 3 ballpoint pens, a multi-tool and the clothing on his back. On top of the keeping hydrated in the intense humidity and relentless heat, Les must cope with deadly snakes, enormous spiders, land-crabs and scorpions.
items.title: Costa Rica

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Survivorman/Survivorman.S01.720p.HDTV.AC3.x264-NTb/Survivorman.S01E04.720p.HDTV.AC3.x264-NTb.mkv
items.summary: The swamplands of Georgia's Altamaha River Basin are all that one would expect of a Primordial bog: dank, menacing, swimming with slithering creepy-crawlies and, of course, alligator-infested. This is the welcoming environment Les Stroud will be immersed in for seven sweaty days and bone-chilling nights.
items.title: Georgian Swamp

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Survivorman/Survivorman.S01.720p.HDTV.AC3.x264-NTb/Survivorman.S01E05.720p.HDTV.AC3.x264-NTb.mkv
items.summary: Pond Inlet, on the Northern reaches of Baffin Island, provides one of the most challenging landscapes our planet has to offer. Over 700km north of the Arctic Circle, it sits amidst grinding, ever-shifting flows of sea-ice where polar-bears roam in search of meat. In this severe climate, Les has been equipped with a bare minimum of raw materials to aid him for the next 7 days - a hunk of uncooked seal-liver, some oil-rich blubber for heat, a seal-hook, three matches, and a knife.
items.title: Canadian Arctic

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Survivorman/Survivorman.S01.720p.HDTV.AC3.x264-NTb/Survivorman.S01E06.720p.HDTV.AC3.x264-NTb.mkv
items.summary: Les is airdropped onto a snow-covered peak in the Canadian Rockies courtesy of the Canadian Mountain Air Rescue Service. They'll come looking for him in seven days. Until then Les is entirely on his own, save for the grizzlies, cougars and wolves that also call this place home. To emulate a real-life survival scenario - in this case a heli-hiking expedition come to grief - Les has been provided with a few readily salvageable items, among them a broken camcorder and tripod. One man's trash is another man's treasure!
items.title: Canadian Rockies

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Survivorman/Survivorman.S01.720p.HDTV.AC3.x264-NTb/Survivorman.S01E07.720p.HDTV.AC3.x264-NTb.mkv
items.summary: The spectacular red landscapes of Utah's canyonlands are as beautiful as they are inhospitable. Like outlaws of old who were known to eat their own horses out of desperation in this forlorn place, Stroud will cannibalize the mountain-bike he has ridden into the middle of nowhere. As well as these scavenged bike parts to aid him, he also has a multi-tool, a magnesium flint-stick and an old energy-bar - that he has a use for other than eating.
items.title: Utah Canyonlands

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Survivorman/Survivorman.S01.720p.HDTV.AC3.x264-NTb/Survivorman.S01E08.720p.HDTV.AC3.x264-NTb.mkv
items.summary: In the remote winter-bound forests of Northern Ontario, a crashed plane lies in the snow beside a frozen lake. There is no one alive on board. But this plane didn't crash here - the decrepit old wreck has been airdropped from a helicopter to provide a temporary home for Survivorman. For a week Les will have to survive in this harsh snowy wilderness with only an axe, a multi-tool and a single blanket to aid him.
items.title: Plane Crash

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Survivorman/Survivorman.S01.720p.HDTV.AC3.x264-NTb/Survivorman.S01E09.720p.HDTV.AC3.x264-NTb.mkv
items.summary: Living "off the land" takes on a new meaning as Les Stroud casts off for a week at sea. With no food and only a bare minimum of equipment, Stroud will be set adrift in an inflatable life raft off the coast of Belize. Battling hunger, thirst and the Caribbean heat, he must also keep his cameras dry to film the ordeal. To top it off - the life raft has a few bad leaks and needs constant bailing. It also leaks air and requires frequent re-inflation with a hand pump - Survivorman is in for a busy few days!
items.title: Lost at Sea

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 01 - Pilot.avi
items.summary: After suffering a series of mysterious anxiety attacks, New Jersey mob boss Tony Soprano agrees to see a psychiatrist, Dr. Jennifer Melfi. As he opens up to the doctor, Tony reveals details about his problems at home and at work that involve his wife Carmela, his kids Meadow and Anthony Jr., his Uncle Junior and his domineering mother Livia.
items.title: The Sopranos

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 02 - 46 Long.avi
items.summary: With acting boss Jackie Aprile dying of cancer, Tony prepares for a power struggle with Uncle Junior. Christopher and his associate Brendan make trouble for themselves when they jack a truck full of DVD players. Tony's mother Livia finally agrees to live in a retirement community. Big Pussy and Paulie Walnuts are sent to find a stolen car.
items.title: 46 Long

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 03 - Denial, Anger, Acceptance.avi
items.summary: Uncle Junior's associate Mikey Palmice stirs things up by making Junior think Tony wants to be next in line for boss. Meanwhile, Tony, Paulie and Silvio deal with Hasidic family problems.
items.title: Denial, Anger, Acceptance

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 04 - Meadowlands.avi
items.summary: Jackie Aprile's health worsens, forcing Tony to make a tough decision. Meanwhile, Anthony Jr. learns the true nature of his father's job in 'waste management.' Also, Tony hires sleazy police lieutenant Vin Makazian to investigate Dr. Melfi's background.
items.title: Meadowlands

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 05 - College.avi
items.summary: During a trip to Maine for Meadow's college interviews, Tony sees a man he believes is a relocated mob snitch. Back at home, Carmela receives comfort from Father Phil.
items.title: College

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 06 - Pax Soprana.avi
items.summary: At Tony's suggestion, Junior is made acting boss after Jackie dies. In therapy, Tony surprises Dr. Melfi with an admission. Carmela and Irina (Tony's mistress) both suffer as Tony's libido takes a nosedive.
items.title: Pax Soprana

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 07 - Down Neck.avi
items.summary: After stealing the 'sacramental wine' from the school chapel, Anthony Jr. is suspended. Tony is concerned that his bad influence is responsible for his son's behavior, and has a series of disturbing flashbacks in which he remembers learning that his own father was in the mob.
items.title: Down Neck

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 08 - The Legend of Tennessee Moltisanti.avi
items.summary: At the wedding of Larry Boy's daughter, the 'boys' find out they're going to be indicted, and make a premature exit to get rid of incriminating evidence at home. Upset that he isn't getting the notoriety of other family members, an agitated Christopher has an ugly encounter with a bakery clerk.
items.title: The Legend of Tennessee Moltisanti

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 09 - Boca.avi
items.summary: Uncle Junior enjoys a romantic tryst in Boca with his girlfriend Bobbi, not realizing that she's been gabbing to her beauty-parlor friends about his oral talents. Meanwhile, controversy arises when Meadow's soccer coach announces he's leaving the school.
items.title: Boca

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 10 - A Hit Is a Hit.avi
items.summary: Christopher and Adrianna cut a deal with a famous gangsta rapper who claims that Hesh pocketed royalties belonging to a cousin who recorded several hit songs decades ago. Meanwhile, Tony plays golf with Cusamano and his white-bread friends.
items.title: A Hit Is a Hit

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 11 - Nobody Knows Anything.avi
items.summary: After Jimmy and Pussy are arrested in an FBI raid, Makazian tells a stunned Tony that Pussy may be wired for the Feds. Tony sends Paulie to find out for sure. Later, Tony learns that Makazian might be trying to frame Pussy to get out of his gambling debts.
items.title: Nobody Knows Anything

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 12 - Isabella.avi
items.summary: Hit men are sent out to whack Tony, who comes out of his depression when he meets Isabella, an Italian exchange student staying next door.
items.title: Isabella

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 13 - I Dream of Jeannie Cusamano.avi
items.summary: In the Season One finale, Tony is stunned to discover that the attempt on his life may have been ordered by someone very close to him. Later, he must deal with the fact that everyone knows he is seeing a shrink. Christopher is sent to take care of Jimmy Altieri.
items.title: I Dream of Jeannie Cusamano

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 01 - Guy Walks into a Psychiatrist's Office.avi
items.summary: Season Two opens with the aftermath of the federal crackdown: Junior's in jail, Melfi refuses to see Tony, Christopher's expanding into new business ventures, Pussy is still missing...and Tony's adjusting to life as the new boss. To complicate matters even more, Tony's free-spirited sister Janice arrives to take care of Livia.
items.title: Guy Walks into a Psychiatrist's Office
items.titleSort: Guy Walks into a Psychiatrist's Office

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 02 - Do Not Resuscitate.avi
items.summary: When black protesters start picketing a construction company that used to be under Uncle Junior's control, Tony meets with the owner--as well as the leader of the protestors--to 'fix' the problem. Meanwhile, Janice gets sucked into Livia's web.
items.title: Do Not Resuscitate

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 03 - Toodle-fucking-oo.avi
items.summary: Tony busts Meadow for partying at his mother's old house. Meanwhile, Ritchie Aprile is out of the can after ten years and looking for action--much to the chagrin of a local pizza-shop owner.
items.title: Toodle-Fucking-Oo

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 04 - Commendatori.avi
items.summary: Tony travels to Italy with Paulie and Christopher to jump-start a car-importing 'business.' While Paulie and Christopher sample some of the Old Country's choicest wares, Tony haggles with the head of a powerful Naples family and recruits a valuable new lieutenant named Furio.
items.title: Commendatori

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 05 - Big Girls Don't Cry.avi
items.summary: Back in Jersey, Furio soon lives up to his name by unleashing his fury on the delinquent proprietor of a local 'tanning salon.' Dr. Melfi shares her guilt over dumping Tony as a client during a session with her own therapist. Meanwhile, Tony learns from Hesh that his father had emotional secrets of his own.
items.title: Big Girls Don't Cry

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 06 - The Happy Wanderer.avi
items.summary: David Scatino, the father of Meadow's friend Eric and the owner of a local sports store, gets on the bad sides of both Richie and Tony when he loses big in two poker games. Paying his respects at a funeral, Tony is forced to deal with the presence of Livia.
items.title: The Happy Wanderer

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 07 - D-Girl.avi
items.summary: With Anthony Jr.'s confirmation approaching, Tony and Carmela find their son's growing apathy a cause for concern. Meanwhile, Christopher's interest in show biz is reignited when he meets a well-known filmmaker through his cousin's girlfriend.
items.title: D-Girl

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 08 - Full Leather Jacket.avi
items.summary: Although Richie is miffed at Tony for forcing him to build a ramp for the pizza-parlor owner he paralyzed, he decides to make a peace offering. Unhappy with their lowly status as Christopher's lackeys, Sean and Matt decide to pledge their allegiance to Richie--through a violent, unexpected act.
items.title: Full Leather Jacket

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 09 - From Where to Eternity.avi
items.summary: Christopher has an out-of-body experience that spooks Paulie to no end. Carmela urges Tony to have a vasectomy. Visiting her own psychiatrist, Melfi reveals the 'unholy alliance' she's made with Tony...as well as her growing dependence on pills and alcohol.
items.title: From Where to Eternity

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 10 - Bust-Out.avi
items.summary: Richie meets with Tony to complain about his end of the garbage business, then meets with Junior to complain about Tony. Later, Tony orchestrates the 'planned bankruptcy' of David Scatino's sporting-goods store while Scatino's wife introduces Carmela to her handsome widowed brother.
items.title: Bust Out

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 11 - House Arrest.avi
items.summary: Having dodged a legal bullet, Tony is advised by his lawyer to spend more time at his businesses. Junior looks for diversions to relieve the tedium of house arrest, and eventually finds one in the company of a police widow. Meanwhile, Melfi's problems boil over while eating dinner with her son.
items.title: House Arrest

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 12 - The Knight in White Satin Armor.avi
items.summary: Engaged lovebirds Richie and Janice have an explosive first quarrel. Meanwhile, Irina takes drastic measures to try to convince Tony to continue their affair.
items.title: The Knight in White Satin Armor

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 13 - Funhouse.avi
items.summary: In the Season Two finale, Tony has a series of 'fever dreams' that help to shed light on some of his problems--particularly his troubles over Big Pussy.
items.title: Funhouse

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 01 - Mr. Ruggerio's Neighborhood.avi
items.summary: While the Soprano family goes about their day-to-day activities, the FBI begins an elaborate operation to bug their home. Tony ponders his options when Patsy starts asking too many questions about his brother's death.
items.title: Mr. Ruggerio's Neighborhood

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 02 - Proshai, Livushka.avi
items.summary: Tony's concerns that his mother will rat him out to the feds expire when she, literally, does. Later, Janice arrives to arrange the funeral, which takes a bizarre turn.
items.title: Proshai, Livushka

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 03 - Fortunate Son.avi
items.summary: Christopher finds that being a 'made' man isn't all it's cracked up to be. Meanwhile, Janice moves into her mother's house, where she soon gets a leg up on Livia's former housekeeper.
items.title: Fortunate Son

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 04 - Employee of the Month.avi
items.summary: Dr. Melfi's attempts to steer Tony into behavior-modification therapy take a detour when a personal crisis gets in the way. Meanwhile, Ralph Cifaretto finds a way to endear himself to Jackie Jr.--but not to Tony.
items.title: Employee of the Month

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 05 - Another Toothpick.avi
items.summary: Bobby 'Bacala' Baccilieri Sr. comes out of retirement to deal with a young hothead named Mustang Sally--much to the chagrin of his son and Uncle Junior.
items.title: Another Toothpick

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 06 - University.avi
items.summary: Ralph's volatile relationship with a Bada Bing stripper and his obsession with the movie 'Gladiator' combine to put a damper on several boys'-nights-out sessions at the club. Meanwhile, at Columbia, Meadow's relationship with Noah is put to the test by her needy roommate Caitlin.
items.title: University

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 07 - Second Opinion.avi
items.summary: Tony convinces Uncle Junior to seek a second opinion for his cancer treatment. Meanwhile, Carmela debates whether or not to take Dr. Melfi's advice and see a shrink, Big Pussy's wife Angie regrets asking Carmela for some money to help her sick dog, and Christopher continues to endure a humiliating probation period at the hands of kinky Paulie.
items.title: Second Opinion

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 08 - He Is Risen.avi
items.summary: As Thanksgiving approaches, Tony's feud with Ralph escalates, despite the intervention of Johnny Sack. At a frat-house mixer, Meadow and Jackie Jr. find they have more in common than mob-boss dads.
items.title: He Is Risen

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 09 - The Telltale Moozadell.avi
items.summary: Tony gives Carmela a sapphire ring for her birthday...and Christopher gives Adriana her very own music club. Anthony Jr. gets busted for vandalizing the school swimming pool, but finds the punishment doesn't fit the crime. Tony test-drives a new Mercedes--and the Mercedes saleswoman, Gloria.
items.title: The Telltale Moozadell

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 10 - To Save Us All from Satan's Power.avi
items.summary: A somnolent visit with the ghosts of Christmas past lands Tony back on Melfi's couch. With the annual pork-store holiday party approaching, Bacala reluctantly agrees to don the Santa suit that Pussy used to wear. Tony and Furio have a holiday surprise in store for the Russian who roughed up Janice.
items.title: To Save Us All from Satan's Power
items.titleSort: To Save Us All from Satan's Power

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 11 - Pine Barrens.avi
items.summary: Paulie and Christopher are engulfed in a nightmarish journey into the South Jersey woods while trying to collect a debt from a Russian mobster. Meanwhile, Meadow is suspicious that Jackie Jr. is two-timing her, and Tony finds that family demands are jeopardizing his romance with Gloria.
items.title: Pine Barrens

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 12 - Amour Fou.avi
items.summary: Inspired by a tale from Ralph about how his father got 'made,' Jackie Jr. decides to 'make his move' in organized crime by instigating a robbery caper at a local card game. Reminded by Melfi of the psychological parallels between his relationships with Gloria and with his mother, Tony finds it harder and harder to spend time with his 'crazy love.'
items.title: Amour Fou

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 13 - Army of One.avi
items.summary: Yet another academic misstep by A.J. forces his parents to contemplate military school. Tony orders Ralph to deal personally with the Jackie Jr. situation, and later seems to take Ralph's side in a money dispute with Paulie. Once again, the family gathers in Artie Bucco's restaurant, where Meadow reflects on being a Soprano.
items.title: Army of One

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 01 - For All Debts Public and Private.avi

Adriana brings her new friend to the Soprano Sunday dinner, but Adriana has no idea who Danielle is working for. items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 02 - No Show.avi
items.summary: With Paulie in jail, Christopher becomes acting capo, but he gets off to a bad start with Patsy. Still troubled by Jackie Jr.'s death, Meadow contemplates taking a year off from college to travel. Meanwhile, Adriana is in a bind after ending her friendship with Daniele, and Silvio discusses a misunderstanding at a Newark riverfront construction site.
items.title: No-Show

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 03 - Christopher.avi
items.summary: Silvio and Ralph must take care of a planned protest of the Columbus Day parade by a Native American group. At an Italian pride ladies' lunch, Carmela is embarrassed by anti-Mafia remarks. Meanwhile, Ralph deals with new relationship troubles, and Bobby receives some tough news.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 04 - The Weight.avi
items.summary: A disparaging remark about his wife sets Johnny Sack off on a vendetta. Meadow decides to do volunteer work at the South Bronx Law Center; Furio hosts a housewarming party for the gang; Silvio and Chris make an offer to an old-time hit man named Lou DiMaggio; and Tony and Carmela find themselves at odds over the family's bill-consolidation strategy.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 05 - Pie-o-My.avi
items.summary: Checking out Ralph's promising new filly at the track, Tony displays a flair for horse-racing strategy--and discovers an unexpected affinity for the stable life. Adriana finds her rock club being used as a place of business for Chris and his pals. Meanwhile, a court artist incurs the wrath of Uncle Junior, and Janice feeds Bobby in his hour of need.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 06 - Everybody Hurts.avi
items.summary: After hiring an attractive French hostess, Elodi, Artie agrees to loan her brother some money, with interest. Meanwhile, Christopher gets some new responsibilities; Carmela fixes Furio up with an oral hygienist; Anthony Jr. becomes the 'dough boy' of a new rich girlfriend; and Tony receives some unsettling news about an old acquaintance.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 07 - Watching Too Much Television.avi

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 08 - Mergers and Acquisitions.avi

Meanwhile, Furio faces up to his inner feelings during a trip to Italy to see his ailing father; Ralph introduces Tony to his new 'goomar,' Valentina; and Carmela finds a new source of investment income.

items.summary: After a sitdown with Carmine and Johnny Sack, Tony contemplates the future of the HUD partnership. Meanwhile, Paulie blows off steam with an old pal; Janice starts losing patience with the obsessive Bobby; and Melfi ponders the Freudian undercurrents of Tony's latest dreams.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 01 - Pilot.avi
items.summary: Dr. Gregory House, a brilliant diagnostician but devoid of bedside  manner, and his elite team of young medical experts rush to save the  life of a kindergarten teacher who started  speaking gibberish and passed out in front of her class.
items.title: Pilot

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 02 - Paternity.avi
items.summary: Dr. House goes with his gut and performs an unethical act to prove what he suspects to be the link to a teenage lacrosse player's illness in order to save the boy's life.
items.title: Paternity

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 03 - Occam's Razor.avi
items.summary: Dr. House and his team race to save a young man who may have not one, but two illnesses killing him.
items.title: Occam's Razor

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 04 - Maternity.avi
items.summary: A maternity ward epidemic forces House to decide whether to save the life of one child over another.
items.title: Maternity

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 05 - Damned If You Do.avi
items.summary: Dr. House's approach is questioned when he treats a nun for what he believes to be an allergy, not realizing the nun's past is coming back to haunt her.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 06 - The Socratic Method.avi
items.summary: The case of a schizophrenic mom with a deadly disease and her teenage son who have traded caretaking roles holds a special interest for Dr. House.
items.title: The Socratic Method

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 07 - Fidelity.avi
items.summary: Dr. House's diagnosis of a married woman with a rare sleep disorder forces her and her husband to examine their marriage and question their trust for each other.
items.title: Fidelity

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 08 - Poison.avi
items.summary: House and his team have to act fast when a high school student is admitted with a mysterious and lethal poisoning, especially when they discover more teens have been diagnosed with the same deadly illness.
items.title: Poison

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 09 - DNR.avi
items.summary: House has to defend himself when he treats a patient who has legally chosen to refuse treatment.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 10 - Histories.avi
items.summary: Dr. House and the team treat a homeless woman whose worsening symptoms and unknown identity prove to be a complex mystery.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 11 - Detox.avi
items.summary: Dr. House takes Cuddy's challenge to go off his painkillers for a week, but the effects of his withdrawal symptoms may put his patient in danger.
items.title: Detox

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 12 - Sports Medicine.avi
items.summary: A baseball player's comeback is cut short when he breaks his arm and House and his team have to act fast to figure out what is causing major bone loss that's killing the player and his dreams.
items.title: Sports Medicine

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 13 - Cursed.avi
items.summary: Dr. House's young patient believes his illness is the result of a curse while House uncovers important information about Chase's father.
items.title: Cursed

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 14 - Control.avi
items.summary: The hospital's new Chairman of the Board has it out for Dr. House, questioning his importance to the hospital and threatening to eliminate House and his team.
items.title: Control

items.summary: Dr. House and his team race to diagnose a member of the mob and get him well enough to testify and enter the witness protection program while Cuddy works to convince Vogler of House's importance to the hospital.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 16 - Heavy.avi
items.summary: Dr. House and his team try to uncover the reason a 10-year-old has a heart attack while House suspects one of his team is selling him out to Vogler.
items.title: Heavy

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 17 - Role Model.avi
items.summary: House and his team battle to save a presidential hopeful, and House refuses to give in to Vogler's ultimatum when given the chance to save one of his team members.
items.title: Role Model

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 18 - Babies & Bathwater.avi
items.summary: House and his team battle to diagnose a pregnant patient's life-threatening illness, prompting her to make the most emotional decision of her life, and Vogler is determined to fire House.
items.title: Babies & Bathwater

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 19 - Kids.avi
items.summary: House and his team race to diagnose a 12-year-old's illness - an illness with a shocking origin - and House asks Cameron to come back to her job.
items.title: Kids

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 20 - Love Hurts.avi
items.summary: House and his team tackle the case of a young man with a penchant for odd behavior, and House prepares for his date with Cameron.
items.title: Love Hurts

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 21 - Three Stories.avi
items.summary: House must decide whether to take the case of his ex-love's husband and he gives medical students a lecture they'll never forget.
items.title: Three Stories

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 1/House MD Season 1 Episode 22 - Honeymoon.avi
items.summary: House is faced with a problem he may not be able to solve and Stacy returns.
items.title: Honeymoon

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 01 - Acceptance.avi
items.summary: When a Death Row inmate mysteriously and  suddenly collapses after hallucinating, House jumps at the chance to  take the case for its difficulty and because it's "cool."
items.title: Acceptance

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 02 - Autopsy.avi
items.summary: A girl's unimaginable bravery toward her terminal illness makes House suspicious as he puts a life-or-death decision about her case in her young hands.
items.title: Autopsy

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 03 - Humpty Dumpty.avi
items.summary: Cuddy struggles with a case of guilt when her handyman is injured while at her place, and House and his team have to work fast to save the young man's pursuit of the American Dream.
items.title: Humpty Dumpty

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 04 - TB Or Not TB.avi
items.summary: House's patient is willing to die in order to further his social cause.
items.title: TB or Not TB

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 05 - Daddy's Boy.avi
items.summary: Lies between a father and son may prevent House and his team from saving their patient.
items.title: Daddy's Boy

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 06 - Spin.avi
items.summary: House's wheels start turning when a pro-cyclist admits to taking performance-enhancing drugs.
items.title: Spin

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 07 - Hunting.avi
items.summary: A patient with AIDS stalks House to get him to take his case; House and Stacy stalk a mouse in her attic; and Cameron faces a health scare of her own.
items.title: Hunting

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 08 - The Mistake.avi
items.summary: A patient's death prompts an investigation into whether Chase or House may have been responsible for her death.
items.title: The Mistake

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 09 - Deception.avi
items.summary: With Foreman as House's supervisor, the team must figure out if a woman who cried wolf  too many times is really ill.
items.title: Deception

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 10 - Failure to Communicate.avi
items.summary: A journalist's head injury results in unintelligible speech, leaving House and his team at a loss; and the heat is turned up between House and Stacy when they're out of town.
items.title: Failure to Communicate

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 11 - Need To Know.avi
items.summary: While House's staff tries to diagnose a woman whose uncontrollable muscle flailing caused her to crash her car, House and Stacy try to resolve their relationship issues once and for all. Cameron refuses to take her HIV test, wary of the results.
items.title: Need to Know

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 12 - Distractions.avi
items.summary: While a severely burned teenager is admitted and his blood tests come back with strange results, House makes himself the guinea pig in his own unofficial tests of a new drug designed to treat migraines to prove a former medical school colleague is wrong about the drug.
items.title: Distractions

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 13 - Skin Deep.avi
items.summary: House uncovers a startling secret when he treats a teenage supermodel for heroin addiction. Meanwhile, Wilson hopes the increased leg pain in House's leg is an indication his leg nerves are regenerating.
items.title: Skin Deep

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 14 - Sex Kills.avi
items.summary: House takes the case of a man who experienced a seizure but wasn't aware it happened. When the man suffers a heart attack and needs a heart transplant, the team races to diagnose a dead woman's illness so they can harvest her heart to save their living patient.
items.title: Sex Kills

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 15 - Clueless.avi
items.summary: House believes a woman is trying to kill her husband and tries to find the proof to confirm his suspicions. When Wilson moves in with House after separating from his wife, he learns Wilson is a great cook.
items.title: Clueless

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 16 - Safe.avi
items.summary: A teenage heart transplant patient is rushed to the hospital when she has an allergic reaction while living in a "clean" room, and House and Wilson work out the kinks of their new living arrangement.
items.title: Safe

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 17 - All In.avi
items.summary: When a six-year-old boy is brought in with the same symptoms as another patient who died years ago under House's care, House believes the cases are identical and he can predict the course of the boy's illness. Meanwhile, the clinic hosts a poker night to benefit the oncology department.
items.title: All In

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 18 - Sleeping Dogs Lie.avi
items.summary: House has to work fast when a woman comes in with a life-threatening case of insomnia. Meanwhile Cameron is angry at Foreman for stealing an article she worked on.
items.title: Sleeping Dogs Lie

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 19 - House Vs God.avi
items.summary: House treats a 15 year old faith healer, while Wilson feels left out when he finds out House has a weekly poker game.
items.title: House vs. God

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 20 - Euphoria (Part 1).avi
items.summary: When a police officer with a gunshot wound to the head and uncontrollable laughter is admitted, House and the team are baffled. When Foreman begins showing the same symptoms, they race to determine the cause of the illness before Foreman's condition takes the same path.
items.title: Euphoria (1)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 21 - Euphoria (Part 2).avi
items.summary: Foreman continues to experience the same progression of symptoms as the police officer. When he realizes he may be facing imminent death, he calls his father who comes to his son's side. As it comes down to a race against time, House believes the solution to the illness is in the police officer's apartment.
items.title: Euphoria (2)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 22 - Forever.avi
items.summary: A young mother has a seizure while bathing her newborn son and nearly drowns him. House and the team have two cases at one time as they try to save the infant and determine the cause of the mother's seizures.
items.title: Forever

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 23 - Who's Your Daddy.avi
items.summary: A 16-year-old Hurricane Katrina victim suffering from hallucinations as a result of the tragedy is brought to House by his former bandmate who recently found out the girl is his daughter. Although House fears his friend is being scammed, he takes the case. As he works his way through the girl's lies so he can diagnose and treat her, he's forced to tell a few lies of his own.
items.title: Who's Your Daddy?

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 24 - No Reason.avi
items.summary: House is shot by a former patient and must share a recovery room with the gunman.
items.title: No Reason

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 3/House MD Season 3 Episode 01 - Meaning.avi
items.summary: After recovering from his gunshot wounds, House works feverishly on two cases at the same time: a paralyzed man who drove his wheelchair into a swimming pool and a woman who became paralyzed after a yoga session.
items.title: Meaning

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 3/House MD Season 3 Episode 02 - Cane and Able.avi
items.summary: House and the team treat a young boy who claims there is a tracking device in his neck and believes he has been the subject of alien experimentation. Cameron is outraged when she learns Cuddy and Wilson have been lying to House about the diagnosis on his last case.
items.title: Cane & Able

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 3/House MD Season 3 Episode 03 - Informed Consent.avi
items.summary: House puts a well-known medical researcher through a battery of tests to determine why he collapsed in his lab. When the team is unable to diagnose the problem, the doctor asks the team to help him end his life. House is forced to use his cane again after the ketamine has worn off as he deals with a clinic patient's teenaged daughter who has a crush on him.
items.title: Informed Consent

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 3/House MD Season 3 Episode 04 - Lines in the Sand.avi
items.summary: When doctors are unable to diagnose why a severely autistic boy screams loudly for no apparent reason, House takes the case. As the boy's condition worsens, it becomes obvious that House relates to the boy because he has no social niceties.
items.title: Lines in the Sand

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 3/House MD Season 3 Episode 05 - Fools for Love.avi
items.summary: House takes the case of a young woman who has been rushed to the hospital with problems breathing and severe stomach pain after she and her husband were robbed. After her husband collapses, the team believes the couple's illnesses are related. Meanwhile, Michael Tritter, a clinic patient, causes problems for House that could have serious ramifications.
items.title: Fools for Love

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 3/House MD Season 3 Episode 06 - Que Sera Sera.avi
items.summary: The team encounters logistical problems while trying to run tests on a 600-pound man due to his extremely large size. Meanwhile, House spends the night in jail after being arrested by Detective Tritter for various charges, including resisting arrest.
items.title: Que SerÃ¡ SerÃ¡

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 3/House MD Season 3 Episode 07 - Son of a Coma Guy.avi
items.summary: House decides to awaken a comatose patient so he can question the man regarding the family history of his son, who may have a genetic condition and the father is the only living relative. Meanwhile, Wilson confronts House about the stolen prescription pad as Tritter approaches Cameron, Chase, and Foreman in an attempt to divide the team and reveal their loyalties.
items.title: Son of Coma Guy

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 3/House MD Season 3 Episode 08 - Whac - A - Mole.avi
items.summary: An 18-year-old teenager is brought to the hospital after having a heart attack. House reviews the boy's file and believes he has the diagnosis. He then turns the case into a game by sealing his opinion in an envelope and challenging Cameron, Foreman, and Chase to guess House's diagnosis on their own. Meanwhile, Tritter's actions against Wilson continue to strain the oncologist's relationship with House and destroy his ability to practice medicine.
items.title: Whac-A-Mole

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 3/House MD Season 3 Episode 09 - Finding Judas.avi
items.summary: House takes the case of a young girl who has been diagnosed with pancreatitis. When he takes her divorced parents to court to force them to allow treatment because they can't agree, the judge awards guardianship of the girl to Cuddy. Meanwhile, Tritter continues his strategy to force House to admit to his drug use by offering one of the team members a deal.
items.title: Finding Judas

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 3/House MD Season 3 Episode 10 - Merry Little Christmas.avi
items.summary: Wilson arranges for House to make a deal with Tritter, but House refuses. Meanwhile, Cuddy cuts House off Vicodin and removes him from the team's case: a 15-year-old little person who entered the hospital with a collapsed lung and anemia.
items.title: Merry Little Christmas

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 3/House MD Season 3 Episode 11 - Words and Deeds.avi
items.summary: House splits his time between treating a firefighter for uncontrollable shivering, giving Tritter a piece of his mind, and handling his trial for forging prescriptions.
items.title: Words and Deeds

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 3/House MD Season 3 Episode 12 - One Day, One Room.avi
items.summary: While House is forced to work full-time in the clinic and deal with a rape victim who insists on confiding with him, Cameron deals with a terminal cancer patient trying to take advantage of her state of mind.
items.title: One Day, One Room

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 3/House MD Season 3 Episode 13 - Needle in a Haystack.avi
items.summary: House and his staff must deal with a teenage Gypsy boy suffering from inexplicable respiratory distress. However, House has bigger issues on his mind: Cuddy has given away his handicapped spot.
items.title: Needle in a Haystack

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 3/House MD Season 3 Episode 14 - Insensitive.avi
items.summary: It's Valentine's Day, and Cuddy has a blind date. Meanwhile, House leaves ER duty to take the case of a child patient named Hannah.
items.title: Insensitive

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 3/House MD Season 3 Episode 15 - Half-Wit.avi
items.summary: House encounters a brain-damaged musical prodigy with inexplicable abilities while the team faces serious concerns about House's own health.
items.title: Half-Wit

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 3/House MD Season 3 Episode 16 - Top Secret.avi
items.summary: The ex-marine that saved House's life, in a dream he had the day before, is admitted in the hospital with symptoms resembling Gulf War Syndrome. While House is busy dealing with his own health issues, and Chase and Cameron are too busy with each other, the ex-marine gets worse.
items.title: Top Secret
